deck: The main protagonist of the series of the same name and the only male member of the Crystal Gems.
description:
Origin

Steven is a hybrid between Rose Quartz, a Crystal Gem, and Greg Universe, a human. Tragically though, during Steven's birth his mother gave up her physical form in order to bring him into the world. Since then, he's been living with the other gems: Garnet, Amethyst, and Pearl. While with them, Steven has been embarking on several gem missions and learning to control his own gem powers.

Creation

Steven Universe first appears as the title cartoon character on Cartoon Network's "Steven Universe". He was created by Rebecca Sugar, former writer for another Cartoon Network series: Adventure Time. The show premiered in 2013.

Steven made his first comic appearance in Adventure Time 2013 Spoooktacular #1 - Costume Party; Secret 'Stache; Halloween Horticulture; Bad Girl Gone Good, and he would later be a main character in his series' comic titled, "Steven Universe".

Powers & Abilities

Steven has the several abilities that comes from the gem on his navel. His main ability is summoning his gem weapon; a pink shield that that is practically unbreakable and can increases it's size. It can also work as an offensive weapon since it can release concussive shock waves.

Steven's most used ability is the summoning of a protective bubble that surrounds himself as well as the ones he wishes to protect. He's mastered this power perfectly, and can even use it instinctively.

Steven also has healing spit. It can be used to heal injuries on both humans and gems, such as broken legs or cracked gemstones.

Steven can also create plants with sentient life, making them his bodyguards, but this is an ability he has no control over, making it very risky.

Steven has recently gained the ability to float and control over his speed of descent. Although he had trouble controlling this ability at first; he quickly learned how to use it albeit not perfectly.

Like most gems, Steven has superhuman strength and shape-changing, but he has little to no control over this abilities. His strength appears to come in bursts, and he has difficulties getting back to his real form after shape-changing, but it is shown in later episodes that he has improved control over his shape-shifting being capable of elongating his limbs at will.

Being a human-gem hybrid, Steven has resistance to anti-gem technology, such as gem-destabilizers.

deck: A young earth pony who is best friends with Silver Spoon. Together they are constantly making fun of the Cutie Mark Crusaders for not having a Cutie Mark.
description:
Diamond Tiara is the daughter of Filthy Rich and Spoiled Rich (nee Milk). A mean girl type pony, she and her friend Silver Spoon would often make fun of the Cutie Mark Crusaders, calling them Blank Flanks.

She is very manipulative, as seen in "Family Appreciation Day," deliberately making Apple Bloom insecure and embarrassed of her Granny Smith, even though she'd never felt embarrassed by her before. By convincing Apple Bloom that Granny Smith was kooky and weird, she bullied Apple Bloom into believing that she should be ashamed of her family.

In "Ponyville Confidential" she was appointed editor-in-chief of the school paper, the Foal-Free Press, and ordered the Cutie Mark Crusaders to write a gossip column. The Crusaders felt bad about spying on other ponies and exposing their secrets, but Diamond Tiara put more pressure on them, becoming drunk on power. By the end of the episode, Ms. Cheerilee admitted that she obviously gave Diamond Tiara too much power, and stripped her of her editing responsibilities, reducing her to printer operator.

In "Crusaders of the Lost Mark," when running for Student Pony President against Pip Squeak, she became very controlling and abusive of Sliver Spoon, causing her to abandon Diamond Tiara as a friend and costing herself the election. Her mother, Spoiled Rich, scolded her daughter and it is only then we learn that Diamond Tiara's bad attitude comes from her mother. The Cutie Mark Crusaders take pity on her and help her become a better pony.

deck: Apple Bloom's cousin from Manehattan and the fourth member of the Cutie Mark Crusaders.
description:
Babs Seed is a cousin of the Apples, from Manehattan. She comes to visit Ponyville in the episode "One Bad Apple," where she is invited to join the Cutie Mark Crusaders. Before she feels fully accepted in her new group of friends, Diamond Tiara and Silver Spoon come in and start picking on them, and Babs sides with them, becoming a bully. The Cutie Mark Crusaders attempt to get back at her, but Applejack informs them that Babs was being bullied a lot in Manehattan, and that's why she came to Ponyville. The Crusaders realize that she only became a bully so as to avoid BEING bullied, and they work things out.

Later on, they get a letter from Babs Seed, informing them that she got her Cutie Mark; a pair of scissors, indicating that she'll probably grow up to be a famous hair stylist.

deck: Granack is the leader of Prixiam Nol-Anj's former clann and a close ally to Nol-Anj herself.
description:
Granack is the leader of a clann of scavengers and contraband pirates that reside in the outer territory of space sector 0563, a barren world unworthy of a name. He and his clann once belonged to a larger group that has apparently died off from unknown causes. Until Prixiam Nol-Anj arrived, Granack's clann survived off of the land and an old cache of food.

The Prixiam

Granack and his clann are patroling their borders when Prixiam Nol-Anj, at first mistaken for a raider ship, lands. Granack immediately recognizes her and explains that the last time anyone saw Nol-Anj was when 'your braids were still short and mine grayer,' and ordered his men to show some respect. The relationship between Granack and Nol-Anj seems to be a close one, as she notes that she and Granack have always trusted one another. Also, when Nol-Anj's ring malfunctions during Hal Jordan's attack, Granack's first instinct is to "Protect the Prixiam."
name: Granack

deck: Lantern Cossite was a guard of the Oan sciencells. He was seduced and subsequently murdered by Prixiam Nol-Anj, who used him as an escape.
description:
Lantern Cossite was Vilgashian, a race that lives on fourteen worlds across four sectores and comprised of approximately two hundred billion beings. He guarded the Oan sciencells until Prixiam Nol-Anj seduced him and tricked him into believing she loved him. Under this impression, he released her, where he watched a star sapphire ring choose Nol-Anj, which only solidified his belief of her love. Moments later, though, she used her new powers to kill him.

When the lanterns later found him, dead, he was being gnawed on by Larfleeze's constructs in the mess hall.
name: Cossite

deck: Costumed hero based in Spain.
description:
Origin

Born in Bangladesh, Montpellier and his family immigrated to Spain when the boy was only three years old, settling in Barcelona. Little else is known about his origin. He was apparently born with his unique fighting ability. At some point he became a crime-fighter, occasionally teaming up with the other Barcelona-based hero, La Sangre.

Creation

Montpellier was created by writer James Robinson and artist Javier Pulido. He first appeared in The Shade #6. He draws heavy inspiration from the Montpellier snake.

Major Story Arcs

The Shade

Montpellier offers his assistance to La Sangre and the Shade, who are attempting to respond to a hostage situation set in motion by the Inquisitor. Using his detective abilities he uncovers the significance of the locations that the Inquisitor had sent a number of his acolytes to commit suicide at. He joins in the assault on the Inquisitor's stronghold at the Sagrada Família, helping to subdue a number of the Inquisitor's acolytes. He is injured in the fighting, but nonetheless uncovers a minor technicality in the location of one of the suicides which undoes the dark-baptism ritual that the Inquisitor had been attempting. This allows the Shade to destroy the Inquisitor's bomb and defeat the villain.

Powers and Abilities

Montpellier has an inborn capacity for an agile, "snaky" form of fighting. He also utilizes artificial venom blasts, projected from wrist-mounted cannons. He is extremely intelligent and a very gifted detective.
name: Montpellier

She was eventually brought by Fred Van Lente into the new IDW Publishing continuity with G.I. Joe #1.

About

Niece of the original Doc "Carl Greer". Joined G.I. Joe after graduating from Wayne State University.

deck: G.I. Joe Telecommunications Expert, Currently assigned to Scarlett's Special Missions Task Force.
description:
See Dial-Tone for the original Real American Hero version

Creation

During IDW Publishing's reboot of G.I. Joe they decided along with Hasbro to recreate the original Dial-Tone as a female character. In the G.I. Joe Rise of Cobra game it is mentioned she is Dial-Tone's sister, but this has not been revealed in the IDW continuity.

About

Dial Tone was originally just one of the "Frobbits" staffing The Pit. When her expert knowledge with telecommunications was noticed and she joined the Special Missions Team under the leadership of Scarlett. She is an invaluable member of the G.I. Joe fighting force. She currently holds the rank of Corporal (E-4)in the United States Army.

Other Media

Television

G.I. Joe Resolute

Dial-Tone is a young telecomunications expert and in the United States Marine Corps. In Resolute she works primarily behind a desk and shows her prowess out by locating both locations of Cobra Commander's bases for firing his weapon. She came up with 5 theories as to how COBRA was staging its attacks. She also explained to Flint how COBRA was blocking satellite communication while still allowing radio signals to get through.

Film

G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra

Dial Tone had a minor appearance in the 2009 film when the G.I. Joe team was attacking the MARS base in the Arctic where Rip-Cord was destroying the nanomite. She was in the command room of Tthe Pit locating the missiles for Hawk.

Games

G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra

In the video game based on the film from, Dial Tone appears as a support character. Her data file states that her real name is "Jill J. Morelli," and that she took over her brother's (Dial-Tone) post on the team after he disappeared on a mission. She is voiced by Aimee Miles.

deck: Astral is a psiot with the power to project her mind out of her body. She is a member of Generation Zero and a former prisoner of Project Rising Spirit.
description:
Creation

Astral was created by writer Joshua Dysart and artist Khari Evans.

Powers

Lady Astral performs a kind of hyper-astral projection. Not only can she create an invisible "psiot package" which allows her consciousness to travel outside of her body, fly around and just generally observe things, but she can also fire her psyche at a person like a bullet, causing all kinds of violent destabilizing flash cognition and even brain-wide seizures.
